Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease one 9x13 inch casserole dish. Break cauliflower into florets, place in large covered saucepan and steam until tender. Place cauliflower in casserole dish; gently stir in sour cream and cheese. In a saute pan over medium heat, melt butter; add bread crumbs and evenly coat. Sprinkle bread crumbs over cauliflower mixture and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.